As a senior software engineer, you are mentoring a junior engineer who is working on a project. The project involves a software that generates a sequence of numbers. The sequence starts with 0 and 1, and each subsequent number is the sum of the previous two numbers. This sequence is known as the Fibonacci sequence.

The junior engineer is trying to write a function in Haxe language that takes an integer n as input and returns the nth number in the Fibonacci sequence. However, he is having trouble with the base case of the recursion.

He has written the following code:

```haxe
function fibonacci(n: Int): Int {
    if (n <= 1) {
        return n;
    } else {
        return fibonacci(n - 1) + fibonacci(n - 2);
    }
}
```

However, when he runs his PicoTest tests, he finds that the function returns incorrect results for n = 0 and n = 1. He asks for your help to correct the base case of the recursion.

What should the base case of the recursion be in order to correctly compute the Fibonacci sequence?

